N.Y. Comp. Codes R. & Regs. Tit. 10 ยง 451.258 - Unit of service

State Regulations
A unit of measure, often commonly accepted, for
determining average cost, time or efficiency, thus making possible: (a) comparisons of one operation with
another, or with the same operation in a preceding period; and
(b) estimates of future operations. Notes
